#!/usr/bin/env python3

"""
Run smoke tests - basic use-case checks with default data

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smoke_testing_(software)

Usage:

    ./dev/run-smoke-tests <path_to_treetime_executable> [--only-failures] [--no-stats]

Options:
    --only-failures    Show only failed tests
    --no-stats         Omit performance statistics

NOTE: you must build and re-build the tested executable yourself, this script does not do that


How to add more tests:

1. Add ancestral commands by adding entries to `ANCESTRAL_BATCH_RUNS`
2. Add clock commands by adding entries to `CLOCK_BATCH_RUNS`
3. Add mugration commands by adding entries to `MUGRATION_BATCH_RUNS`
4. Add arbitrary commands to `make_additional_commands()`

"""

